  'searchDescription' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => 'Journal of Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory is a peer-reviewed journal which publishes, since 1972, original papers in all areas of Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory.',
  ),
  'description' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => '<ul><li>is a peer-reviewed journal which publishes, <strong>since 1972</strong>, original papers in all areas of Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory;</li><li>is edited at <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro">"Tiberiu Popoviciu" Institute of Numerical Analysis</a> (Romanian Academy) and printed at the <a href="http://www.ear.ro">Publishing House of the Romanian Academy</a>;</li><li>its former name is <strong><em>Revue d\'Analyse Numérique et de Théorie de l\'Approximation </em></strong>(see the <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/jnaat/journal/about/history">history</a> section);</li><li>all its papers are freely available at the "<a href="/jnaat/journal/issue/archive">free archives</a>" section, either scanned (1972-2000), or latex-pdf (since 2001);</li><li>the <strong>papers</strong> are <strong>not</strong> necessarily in <strong>final</strong> pdf version (DOI\'s, hyperrefs to be added to the refs, some scanned papers to be retyped); version of each pdf posted soon;</li><li>further submissions of manuscripts <strong>should not</strong> be sent <strong>by e-mail</strong>, but by <a href="/jnaat/journal/user/register">registering</a> (check the "as author" option), and then by uploading the files.</li></ul>',
  ),
  'history' => 
  array (
    'en_US' => '<div><ul><li>2015-present<br />Full title: <strong><em>Journal of Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory<br /></em></strong><a href="http://www.ams.org/msnhtml/serials.pdf">AMS abbreviated title</a>: <em>J. Numer. Anal. Approx. Theory<br /></em>ISSN 2457-6794, ISSN-L 2457-6794, ISSN-E 2501-059X</li><li>1992-2014<br />Full title: <strong><em>Revue d\'analyse numérique et de théorie de l\'approximation<br /></em></strong><a href="http://www.ams.org/msnhtml/serials.pdf">AMS abbreviated title</a>: <em>Rev. Anal. Numér. Théor. Approx</em>.<br />ISSN 1222-9024, ISSN-L 1222-9024, ISSN-E 2457-8126</li><li>1975-1991<br />Full title: <strong><em>Mathematica - Revue d\'analyse numérique et de théorie de l\'approximation. L’analyse numérique et la théorie de l\'approximation<br /></em></strong><a href="http://www.ams.org/msnhtml/serials.pdf">AMS abbreviated title</a>: <em>Anal. Numér. Théor. Approx</em>.<br />ISSN 1010-3376, ISSN-L 1010-3376, ISSN-E 2457-8118</li><li>1972-1974<br />Full title: <strong><em>Revue d\'analyse numérique et de la théorie de l\'approximation<br /></em></strong><a href="http://www.ams.org/msnhtml/serials.pdf">AMS abbreviated title</a>:<em> Rev. Anal. Numér. Théorie Approximation<br /></em>ISSN 0301-9241, ISSN-L 0301-9241, ISSN-E 2457-810X</li></ul></div><p> </p><p>The journal has been founded by acad. <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">Tiberiu Popoviciu</a> in 1972, under the name <strong><em>Revue d\'analyse numérique et de la théorie de l\'approximation.</em></strong> Notice the sequence “<em>et de la théorie”, </em>which will change later into “<em>et de théorie”. </em>The journal was born at the <em>Institute of Numerical Analysis, Romanian Academy, </em>also founded by <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu</a>, in 1957 (today the Institute bears his name; in Romanian: <em>Institutul de Calcul “Tiberiu Popoviciu” al Academiei Române</em> – <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/" target="_new">ICTP</a>).</p><p>In 1972 <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu</a> founded another journal,  <a href="/ranta-ro-72-74"><strong><em>Revista de Analiză Numerică şi Teoria Aproximaţiei</em></strong></a>, with name and papers published in Romanian, which had appeared for only three years (1972-1974; see below). The journal  can be identified by the AMS abbreviation <em>Rev. Anal. Numer. Teoria Aproximaţiei</em>. Though the two journals had the same names but in two different languages (French, resp. Romanian), their content was not related one to another, as it can be easily seen from <a href="/ranta-ro-72-74">the journal website</a> (the scanned papers are freely available). It is interesting to note that <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu</a> had published one paper only in the later journal (<a href="/ranta-ro-72-74/journal/article/view/1972-v1-n1-Popoviciu"><em>Asupra unor formule de medie</em></a>, in Romanian; see also <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu\'s website</a> for notes on this paper).</p><p><strong>Premises.</strong> The foundation of two journals was a natural step, since, after the coming of <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu</a> to Cluj, in 1946, he developed strong teams working in Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory, both at the Institute and at the <a href="http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/profesor-tiberiu-popoviciu/">“Babeş-Bolyai” University</a>, where he taught. <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">T. Popoviciu</a> also developed a hardware section at the Institute; three original computers were built here from scratch between 1957-1968 (the first, MARICA in 1959, was a prototype, the second, DACICC-1, 1959-1963, was the first computer in our country containing transistors and having internal memory based on ferrites, and the third, DACICC-200, 1964-1968, fully tranzistorized, had the best characteristics in our country in the sixties). Romania was then among the eight countries making computers. By the beginning of seventies, the Institute attained its full development; each year it increased by joining the most talented of the graduates of the University, until it reached nearly 50 people. During 1957-1975, the Institute hosted six international conferences, with numerous and important participants from abroad (e.g., <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Erd%C5%91s">P. Erdős</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isaac_Jacob_Schoenberg">I. Schoenberg</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Dieudonn%C3%A9">J. Dieudonne</a>, etc.). See here more aspects and pictures from the history of ICTP (to be completed).</p><p>In 1975, in “a momentary lapse of reason”, the communist president N. <span>Ceaușescu</span> dissolved all the three mathematical institutes of the Romanian Academy (at Bucharest, Iaşi and Cluj-Napoca). The reasons were obviously subjective (his daughter, Zoe, was working at the Institute of Mathematics from Bucharest), and were not connected to the outstanding activity and results obtained by the institutes.</p><p>Moreover, out of three mathematical journals edited at Cluj-Napoca under the auspices of the Romanian Academy (the two journals mentioned above, plus <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/mathem"><em>Mathematica</em></a>) the communist regime allowed only one. Curiously enough, the request of the mathematicians that the journals <em>Rev. Anal. Numér. Théorie Approximation</em> and <em>Mathematica</em> to merge into a single one, with merged titles (but different subtitles, and with unchanged number of issues per year), was approved (sic!). In this way, the results in Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory continued to be published in the journal <strong><em>Mathematica - Revue d\'analyse numérique et de théorie de l\'approximation. L’analyse numérique et la théorie de l\'approximation</em></strong>. The Editorial Board remained unchanged.</p><p>These tragic events caused the death of T. Popoviciu (as well as of acad. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miron_Nicolescu">Miron Nicolescu</a>, in Bucharest, and of acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mendel_Haimovici">Mendel Haimovici</a> in Iaşi).</p><p>Starting from 1992, both “merged” journals took back their names. Our journal continued to appear with the name <strong><em>Revue d\'analyse numérique et de théorie de l\'approximation.</em></strong> Notice the sequence “<em>et de théorie”, </em>which was changed from “<em>et de la théorie”</em>  that appeared between 1972-1974.</p><p>A final change of title of this journal was made in 2015, when the title was translated in English: <strong><em>Journal of Numerical Analysis and Approximation Theory</em></strong>. The whole content of the journal was digitized, and set up under the OJS system.</p><p> </p><p>The Editors-in-Chief have been, sequentially,</p><ul><li>acad. Tiberiu Popoviciu (not on paper, but behind), its founder;</li><li>prof. Elena Popoviciu (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caius_Iacob">Caius Iacob</a> (Bucharest and Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-1991; director in 1992;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicolae-Victor_Teodorescu">Nicolae Teodorescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): director between 1993-2001;</li><li>prof. <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/pavaloiu">Ion Păvăloiu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1992-2001;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimitrie_D._Stancu">Dimitrie D. Stancu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 2002-2014. </li></ul><p>At present, the Editors-in-Chief are prof. <a href="http://math.ubbcluj.ro/~agratini" target="_new">Octavian Agratini</a> and dr. <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/catinas" target="_new">Emil Cătinaş</a>.</p><p>The deputy Editors-in-Chief have been, sequentially,</p><ul><li>prof. Elena Popoviciu (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-2001;</li><li>prof. <a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/pavaloiu">Ion Păvăloiu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): since 2001; </li></ul><p>We also present, alphabetically, the list of the former and present members of the <a href="/jnaat/journal/about/editorialTeam">Editorial Board</a>:</p><ul><li><a href="http://www.dm.uniba.it/Members/altomare/">Francesco Altomare</a> (Bari, Italy): 1998-;</li><li><a href="http://www.cameron.edu/~ioannisa/">Ioannis K. Argyros</a> (Cameron, USA): 2013-;</li><li>Oleg Aramă (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1991;</li><li>Wolfgang Breckner (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/catinas" target="_new">Emil Cătinaş</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 2013-;</li><li>Stefan Cobzaş (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 2013-;</li><li>Gheorghe Coman (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ioan_Cuculescu">Ioan Cuculescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://math.ubbcluj.ro/~dduca/">Dorel Duca</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="https://www.uni-due.de/mathematik/aggonska/gonska.shtml">Heinz H. Gonska</a> (Duisburg, Germany): 1998-;</li><li><a href="http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Laura_Gori">Laura Gori</a> (Rome, Italy): 1998-;</li><li><a href="http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/profesor-sever-aurel-groze/">Sever Groze</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-1991;</li><li><a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolf_Haimovici">Adolf Haimovici</a> (...): 1977-1991;</li><li><a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dumitru_Ionescu">Dumitru V. Ionescu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-1986;</li><li><a href="http://users.utcluj.ro/~ivan/">Mircea Ivan</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1987-1991;</li><li><a href="http://www.math.uaic.ro/index.php?id=401&amp;cod=76">Constantin Ilioi</a> (Iaşi, Romania): 1998-;</li><li>acad. <a href="http://www.acad.ro/pag_cv/cv_miosifescu.htm">Marius Iosifescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 1992-;</li><li><a href="https://hu.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalik_K%C3%A1roly">Carol Kalik</a> (??, Romania): 1977-1986;</li><li>acad. <a href="http://www.imar.ro/~smarcus/">Solomon Marcus</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 1993-;</li><li><a href="http://www.ima.ro/people/gmarinoschi.html">Gabriela Marinoschi</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/profesor-ioan-marusciac/">Ioan Maruşciac</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Giuseppe_Mastroianni">Giuseppe Mastroianni</a> (Potenza, Italy): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://www.math.uvt.ro/personal/maruster.stefan">Stefan Maruster</a> (Timişoara, Romania): 1998-;</li><li><a href="http://www.math.uvt.ro/personal/megan.mihail">Mihail Megan</a> (Timişoara, Romania): 2013-;</li><li>acad. <a href="http://www.mi.sanu.ac.rs/~gvm/">Gradimir V. Milovanovic</a> (Nis, Serbia): 1998-;</li><li><a href="http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/profesor-emil-muntean/">Emil Munteanu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/mustata/">Costica Mustata</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="https://hu.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%A9meth_S%C3%A1ndor_(matematikus)">Alexandru N<span>é</span>meth</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1992-2012;</li><li><a href="http://camo.ici.ro/neculai/nandrei.htm">Andrei Neculai</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li>Ladislau Nemeti (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li>Andrei Ney (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.cs.ubbcluj.ro/profesor-arpad-pal/">Arpad Pal</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-1991;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miron_Nicolescu">Miron Nicolescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.mariorosariooccorsio.com/site/scientifiche/">Mario Rosario Occorsio</a> (??, Italy): 1998-2012;</li><li><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/pavaloiu" target="_new">Ion Păvăloiu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1974-1977;</li><li>Vasile Peteanu (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li><span>acad. </span><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/popoviciu">Tiberiu Popoviciu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1975;</li><li><a href="http://www.aos.ro/site_mod/Primapagina/CV-uriMembri/s1-Titus-Petrila.pdf">Titus Petrila</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1992-2012;</li><li><a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Ioan_Rasa">Ioan Rasa</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1987-1991;</li><li>Dumitru Ripeanu (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1972-1977;</li><li>Ioan A. Rus (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-1991;</li><li>acad. <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimitrie_D._Stancu">Dimitrie D. Stancu</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1977-2001;</li><li>acad. <a href="http://www.imar.ro/~isinger/">Ivan Singer</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 1993-;</li><li>acad.  <a href="https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicolae-Victor_Teodorescu">Nicolae Teodorescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 1977-1992;</li><li><a href="https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Stefan_Tigan">Stefan Tigan</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1974-1977;</li><li><a href="http://www.win.tue.nl/~pop/">Iuliu Sorin Pop</a> (Eindhoven, Holland): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://www.math.umbc.edu/~potra/">Florian Potra</a> (Baltimore, USA): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://fmi.unibuc.ro/ro/preda_vasile/">Vasile Preda</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://inf.ucv.ro/~radulescu/" target="_new">Vicenţiu Rădulescu</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://perso.univ-perp.fr/sofonea/">Mircea Sofonea</a> (Perpignan, France): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://csm.ro/web/stancum/">Ioan Stancu-Minasian</a> (Bucharest, Romania): 2013-;</li><li><a href="https://math.temple.edu/~szyld/">Daniel Szyld</a> (Temple, USA): 2013-;</li><li><a href="http://www6.cityu.edu.hk/ma/people/profile/zhoudx.htm">Ding Xuan Zhou</a> (Hong-Kong, P.R. China): 2013-.</li></ul><p> The secretaries of the Editorial Board:</p><ul><li><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/catinas" target="_new">Emil Cătinaş</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1998-2012;</li><li><a href="http://math.ubbcluj.ro/~dduca/">Dorel Duca</a> (Cluj-Napoca, Romania): 1987-2012;</li><li><a href="http://www.ictp.acad.ro/craciun/index.htm">